name: glycerate 2-kinase
classes: Phosphotransferases with an alcohol group as acceptor
comment: A key enzyme in the nonphosphorylative Entner-Doudoroff pathway in archaea [1,2]. In the bacterium Hyphomicrobium methylovorum GM2 the enzyme is involved in formaldehyde assimilation I (serine pathway) [5]. In Escherichia coli the enzyme is involved in D-glucarate/D-galactarate degradation [6]. The enzyme requires a divalent metal ion [1].
